{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "An answer to each prompt is greedily generated up to 2048 tokens by the evaluated model.",
    "Model responses are then compared with responses from GPT-4-0314 using GPT-4-1106-preview judge to calculate a win-rate over GPT-4-0314.",
    "All experiments were conducted using the Nemo-Aligner framework (Shen et al., 2024), specifically with the container (nvcr.io/nvidia/nemo:24.05.llama3.1).",
    "We train models with a max sequence length of 4096 and discard any data longer than this, which only consists of less than 3% of each dataset.",
    "In all experiments, we use AdamW optimizer (Loshchilov and Hutter, 2017) with 10 warmup steps."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "All experiments were conducted using the Nemo-Aligner framework (Shen et al., 2024), specifically with the container (nvcr.io/nvidia/nemo:24.05.llama3.1).",
